     1	//! fmap URL encoding/decoding module.
     2	//!
     3	//! Implements bitpacked route tokens compatible with the frontier-reapers/starmap specification
     4	//! and its JavaScript reference implementation (`bitpacking.js`).
     5	//!
     6	//! **Waypoint type bit width**
     7	//!
     8	//! The starmap format defines 5 waypoint types (0-4), where type 4 (`SetDestination`)
     9	//! represents gate-to-gate jump sequences. Correct encoding therefore requires **3 bits**
    10	//! for the waypoint type field.
    11	//!
    12	//! Some older C# code used only 2 bits for waypoint type and masked values with `& 0b11`,
    13	//! which silently corrupts type 4 into type 0 during encoding/decoding. This Rust
    14	//! implementation intentionally uses 3 bits to match the starmap specification and
    15	//! JavaScript reference, and may not be compatible with any legacy 2-bit C# encoders.
    16	//!
    17	//! See: https://github.com/frontier-reapers/starmap/blob/main/docs/ROUTE_FEATURE.md
    18	
